{"image_id": "CINF_2012_page_63", "image_size": [1275, 1650], "ocr": [{"text": "Cincinnati Financial Corporation – 2012 10-K - 61", "bbox": [461.2, 1600.4, 840.9, 1622.7]}, {"text": "property-oriented lines of business. The executive risk portion of bond and executive risk showed", "bbox": [150.0, 58.4, 1048.0, 86.0]}, {"text": "improvement in 2012, after experiencing several years of unfavorable effects from the U.S. credit crisis of", "bbox": [150.0, 82.4, 1123.2, 110.0]}, {"text": "2008. Since the credit crisis, many of our financial institution policies have been nonrenewed, reducing", "bbox": [150.0, 106.4, 1098.1, 134.0]}, {"text": "exposure for this portion of our bond and executive risk business.", "bbox": [150.0, 130.1, 762.3, 157.8]}, {"text": "Commercial Casualty", "bbox": [150.0, 159.6, 379.0, 191.6]}, {"text": "Commercial casualty is our largest line of business and has in recent years maintained a very satisfactory", "bbox": [150.0, 690.1, 1127.0, 717.7]}, {"text": "total loss and loss expense ratio. Premiums grew in 2012, compared with 2011, largely due to higher pricing", "bbox": [150.0, 714.1, 1149.0, 741.8]}, {"text": "and premium growth initiatives that helped new business written premiums grow nearly 20 percent. During", "bbox": [150.0, 738.1, 1132.7, 765.8]}, {"text": "2011, our underwriters began fully using predictive modeling tools for general liability coverages in our", "bbox": [150.0, 761.9, 1094.6, 789.5]}, {"text": "commercial package accounts, and we believe these tools are improving our pricing precision.", "bbox": [150.0, 785.9, 1023.3, 813.5]}, {"text": "Improving economic conditions also contributed to growth through higher premiums from audits that", "bbox": [150.0, 816.2, 1072.4, 843.8]}, {"text": "confirmed or adjusted initial premium estimates. As discussed in the commercial lines insurance premiums", "bbox": [150.0, 840.2, 1136.3, 867.8]}, {"text": "section of Commercial Lines Insurance Results of Operations, Page 57, economic trends cause", "bbox": [150.0, 864.2, 1035.4, 891.8]}, {"text": "corresponding changes in underlying insured exposures, including general liability coverage where the", "bbox": [150.0, 888.2, 1098.2, 915.8]}, {"text": "premium amount is heavily influenced by economically-driven measures of risk exposure such as", "bbox": [150.0, 911.9, 1049.4, 939.6]}, {"text": "sales volume.", "bbox": [150.0, 936.0, 289.0, 963.6]}, {"text": "The 2012 total loss and loss expense ratio improved by 10.2 percentage points, largely due to lower current", "bbox": [150.0, 966.2, 1145.6, 993.8]}, {"text": "accident year losses and loss expenses and higher earned premiums. Favorable development on prior", "bbox": [150.0, 990.2, 1100.2, 1017.8]}, {"text": "accident year reserves continued in 2012 at a significant level, reflecting further moderation in loss cost", "bbox": [150.0, 1014.2, 1103.9, 1041.8]}, {"text": "trends, particularly for umbrella liability coverage included in many commercial package accounts.", "bbox": [150.0, 1038.2, 1055.0, 1065.8]}, {"text": "Development trends are further discussed in Consolidated Property Casualty Insurance Development of", "bbox": [150.0, 1062.0, 1112.2, 1089.6]}, {"text": "Estimated Reserves by Accident Year, Page 92.", "bbox": [150.0, 1086.0, 600.5, 1113.6]}, {"text": "The 2011 current accident year loss and loss expense ratio before catastrophe losses improved by", "bbox": [149.9, 1116.2, 1063.9, 1143.9]}, {"text": "10.4 percentage points compared with accident year 2010, largely reflecting higher earned premiums from", "bbox": [149.9, 1140.3, 1133.1, 1167.9]}, {"text": "improving economic trends and pricing that offset normal loss cost inflation. In addition, the refined line of", "bbox": [149.9, 1164.3, 1122.4, 1191.9]}, {"text": "business allocation process for loss expenses reduced the 2011 ratio by approximately 4 percentage points.", "bbox": [149.9, 1188.3, 1150.5, 1215.9]}, {"text": "(Dollars in millions)", "bbox": [96.4, 196.6, 202.1, 213